cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the impacts of smart inverters on distribution feeders and their behavior under increasing PV penetration, which involves control and regulation of the power system. 
- cs.PF (Power and Energy): The paper specifically focuses on the impacts of PV penetration on distribution feeders and how smart inverters can mitigate these impacts, which falls under the domain of power and energy. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper involves simulations of deployment scenarios of smart inverters on a real distribution feeder, which could potentially involve distributed computing techniques. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the use of smart inverters as an emerging technology to address the impacts of high PV penetration on distribution feeders. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves computational simulations of the impacts of smart inverters on a real distribution feeder, which falls under the domain of computational engineering.
